CBRE Agribusiness are pleased to present for sale Bogolara a prime grazing landholding located on the transition from the Southern Tablelands and South West Slopes regions of New South Wales.

The property comprises a total area of 1,667* hectares of undulating granite grazing country supporting productive pastures underpinned by the reliable 700*mm annual average rainfall, providing favourable growing conditions for fodder crops and pastures.

KEY INVESTMENT HIGHLIGHTS

History
Part of the renowned "Bogolara Run" first offered for selection under the Free Selection Act 1861.

Scale of Operation
A large versatile and productive grazing property with some farming options, suitable for sheep and cattle breeding and fattening.

Location 
Located only 7*km from the Hume Highway and a convenient distance from the major service towns of Yass, Gundagai and Harden. A comfortable three* hour freeway drive from the M5/M7 intersection at Sydney. 

Water 
Secure water for stock and domestic purposes via multiple sources.

Scenically attractive
Ranging from soft valley floors to gently undulating country and steeper hillsides. Large scattered box trees and groves of remnant native timber provide shelter for livestock and a classic Australian rural vista.

Recent infrastructure investments
Benefit from significant recent investments in productivity and water security, including new ProWay  sheep yards, 8*km of new internal fencing, internal formed roads and ramps to facilitate easy access around the property, new bore and reticulated water system. 

Accommodation 
Two homes, one recently renovated provide owner's and manager's accommodation.

Bogolara is a noted property of the district, and possesses all of the key features required to operate a profitable agricultural enterprise boasting fertile soils, a favourable climate and reliable water supply from multiple sources. 

Bogolara will be offered for sale via Auction at 11 am Australian Eastern Daylight Time (AEDT), Monday 19 December 2016 at the CBRE Auction Rooms, 12/14 Moore Street Canberra ACT.

CBRE Agribusiness is pleased to present for sale Billabong, a productive 907* hectare mixed farming property located on the eastern edge of the renowned South West Slopes Region of New South Wales.

Billabong has been held in single family ownership since 1935. Long term family ownership is common in the Yass district with up to 5th generation farming families dominating ownership of the local land holdings.

Billabong is a true mixed farming platform providing the option for any combination of cropping and grazing enterprises allowing flexibility to capitalise on seasonal and market variations.  

KEY FEATURES

•	Superb location to markets, service suppliers and social amenities
•	True mixed farming land providing flexibility of enterprise choice
•	Historic production figures demonstrate a carrying capacity of 9,000* DSE
•	Working improvements & laneways facilitate ease of management of all cropping, sheep and cattle enterprises
•	5.5* kilometres of Boorowa River frontage
•	Comfortable homestead set in established gardens
•	81 years of single family ownership
•	Settlement date 31 October 2016

Billabong is positioned 30* radial kilometres north of Yass on White Flag Lane. The property is also conveniently located to the following major regional centres:

Binalong				approximately 10* radial kilometres 
Boorowa				approximately 20* radial kilometres
Canberra				approximately 85* radial kilometres
Batemans Bay	(South Coast)	approximately 180* radial kilometres
Jindabyne (Snow fields)		approximately 200* radial kilometres
Sydney M5/M7 Intersection	approximately 210* radial kilometres

Grain receival sites are located at Boorowa and Cunningar (30* radial kilometres).

The soon to open South Eastern Livestock Exchange (SELX) located at Yass will provide outstanding marketing opportunities for all classes of livestock with minimal freight expenditure. 

For Sale by Public Auction, Thursday 4 August 2016 at 11am Australian Eastern Standard Time (AEST) 

Venue: CBRE Auction Rooms, 12/14 Moore Street Canberra.
